<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple Computer//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  Hardened-runtime entitlements for NocordHF.

  com.apple.security.device.audio-input
    Required so the FT8 receive path can read from the rig's USB
    audio CODEC interface. Without it, hardened-runtime apps get a
    silent denial from CoreAudio and decode nothing — Info.plist's
    NSMicrophoneUsageDescription on its own only governs the user
    consent prompt, not the underlying capability.

  com.apple.security.device.bluetooth
    Required so the MeshCore BLE transport can scan for and connect
    to companion-firmware LoRa radios. Same pattern as audio-input:
    Info.plist's NSBluetoothAlwaysUsageDescription handles the user
    prompt; this entitlement opens the underlying CoreBluetooth API
    under the hardened runtime.

  com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit
  com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory
  com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation
    Standard relaxations for Cgo-backed Go programs (Fyne/glfw):
    the Go runtime allocates W+X memory for some scenarios, malgo's
    miniaudio backend dlopens system frameworks dynamically, and
    library validation refuses to load unsigned helper dylibs that
    Fyne's GL backend pulls in on first frame. Without these,
    hardened-runtime notarized builds either fail to launch on
    Tahoe (XPC paste-telemetry watchdog SIGABRTs during
    +[NSApplication initialize]) or silently break specific
    subsystems (Metal pipeline cache, malgo audio).
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>com.apple.security.device.audio-input</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.device.bluetooth</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key>
    <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
